NAME		mail
SYNTAX		mail
		mail -s [num]
		mail <user>[, user]...
		mail -k
DESCRIPTION	Mail without arguments takes you into the interactive mail
		reader.
		mail -s lists all of your current jobs in the mailspool and,
		    with a supplied message number, despools that message.
		mail -k kicks the mailspool, forcing a resend of all spooled
		    messages.
		The third form sends mail messages to a list of users, a user
		may be either:
			A user's name.
			An intermud address (eg. user@host)
			A grupe id. (eg #friends)
SEE ALSO	grupe
